<refnamediv>
    <refname>glite-eds-get</refname>
    <refpurpose>
        Gets a file using gLite I/O
    </refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
	<command>glite-eds-get</command>

        <group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-h</option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-q</option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
	        <arg choice="plain"><option>-v</option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-s <replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-i <replaceable>ID</replaceable></option></arg>
	</group>
        <arg choice="plain"><option><replaceable>REMOTE_FILE</replaceable></option></arg>
        <arg choice="plain"><option><replaceable>LOCAL_FILE</replaceable></option></arg>

    </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
	<command>glite-eds-get</command> is a command-line tool for transferring a remote file from
	a gLite I/O server to the local filesystem. It is assumed that the file is encrypted on the storage.
        <command>glite-eds-get</command> will look up the key needed for decryption in the hydra catalog,
        retrieve it and decrypt the file. The local file will be decrypted.
    </para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>
    <variablelist>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-h</option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        Show help screen.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-q</option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        Quiet operation.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-v</option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        Verbose operation.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-i <replaceable>ID</replaceable></option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        The ID to use to look up the encryption key in hydra. This defaults to the remote file's GUID.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-s <replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        If <option><replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option> starts with <userinput>gliteio://</userinput>,
		then it it used as the gLite I/O service URL.
		Otherwise <option><replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option> is taken as a service name, and
		serives discovery is used to determine the service endpoint.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
	    <term><option><replaceable>REMOTE_FILE</replaceable></option></term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        The name of the remote file.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
	    <term><option><replaceable>LOCAL_FILE</replaceable></option></term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        The name of the file on the local filesystem.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
</refsect1>

